    ‚úî Proper error handling e.g. incorrect prop/style values - no malformed style prop can throw from `op_flush` any more (a throw there aborted the whole commit batch and wedged the reconciler mid-commit ‚Üí frozen UI). Bad unit-bearing values (`Length`/`Angle`/`Time`/`FontSize`), `Rect` shorthand tokens / value-counts (`padding`/`margin`/`border`/`borderRadius`), and unknown rect/`borderColor` side keys now all warn + fall back to a default instead of erroring (`protocol` uses the neutral `tracing` facade, staying bevy-type-free). The silent enum mappers (`display`/`align*`/`justify*`/`flexDirection`/‚Ä¶ via `unknown_keyword`), grid track parsing, and `fontWeight` now warn on unrecognized values too, matching the existing color/`fontFamily` warn+fallback pattern. NOTE remaining gap: a wrong JSON *type* for a scalar field (`width={{}}`/`width={true}`) still throws from `deserialize_any`; TS guards it (`js/src/jsx.d.ts`), so deferred. Also hardened the hot-reload path (`js_thread.rs`): a rebuilt bundle that throws on execution ‚Äî a syntax error OR a runtime error like `padding: aa16` (undefined identifier) ‚Äî is now REJECTED rather than applied; the loop re-runs the last working bundle (re-parking the event loop) instead of escalating to a destructive full rebuild and then `break`ing the JS thread (which used to freeze the UI permanently with no recovery). Covered by `crates/core/tests/broken_reload.rs`. Remaining: a broken *initial* (cold-start) bundle still can't start (no last-good to fall back to). @done(26-06-30 16:44)
